(I) the Participant's employer-provided Retirement Plan benefit;
 
(II) 100% of the Participant's Primary Social Security Benefit payable at his Social Security Retirement Age, as determined under the provisions of the Social Security Act in effect at the date of the occurrence triggering the determination, assuming that the Participant had continued in the employ of the Company at the annual base salary he was earning at the time such event occurred until what would have been his Social Security Retirement Age ( that in the event of a Change in Control, the offset under this subparagraph (II) shall not apply to any Participant who has completed fewer than 10 years of service at the time of the Change in Control);
provided, however,
 
