On February 5, 2008, Albemarle Corporation (the "Company") entered into a Stock Purchase Agreement (the "Purchase Agreement") with each of (i) William M. Gottwald, John D. Gottwald and James T. Gottwald as Trustees of Floyd, Jr.'s Trust (the "Trust") under the will of Floyd D. Gottwald, (ii) Floyd D. Gottwald, Jr. and (iii) Westham Partners, L.P., pursuant to which the Company agreed to purchase an aggregate of 3,000,000 shares of common stock, $0.01 par value per share ("Common Stock"), of the Company from the Trust, an aggregate of 300,000 shares of Common Stock from Floyd D. Gottwald, Jr., and an aggregate of 700,000 shares of Common Stock from Westham Partners, L.P. each at a price equal to $37.2174, which represents the product of 0.99 multiplied by the average closing price of a share of the Common Stock, as determined by the Company's Chief Financial Officer based on trade data provided by the New York Stock Exchange, for the three trading days ending February 5, 2008. Copies of the Purchase Agreements are attached hereto as Exhibit 10.1, Exhibit 10.2 and 10.3, respectively, and incorporated herein by reference.
 
 
